#!/usr/bin/env n6
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Scope: docs/, design/, papers/ (skynet-timer landing + hexa-os design docs)
# skynet-hexa-os-2026-04-27.n6 — combined absorption shard
#
# Two small repos absorbed in one pass:
#   1. ~/core/skynet-timer (632K) — public landing page, GitHub Pages
#      "Two attractors. One deadline. Φ > Φ_c or Skynet."
#      Static HTML/CSS/JS countdown to AGI 2029 / RSI 2035.
#   2. ~/core/hexa-os (372K) — design-stage AI inference appliance OS
#      "Unikernel + law-enforced + hexa self-host. Serving p99 30-50% ↓."
#
# Prefixes: SKYNET-* (timer/site), HEXA-OS-* (kernel design).
# Implementation status:
#   - skynet-timer: SHIPPED (live site, MIT, multilingual EN/ZH/RU/JA/KO)
#   - hexa-os: DESIGN ONLY (one freestanding probe skeleton, no boot, no kernel)
# Atlas dedup: 0 prior hits for "skynet-timer" or "hexa-os" in atlas.n6.
# Honesty: Φ_c numerical anchor present (≈ 0.5 IIT empirical) — see
#          SKYNET-PHI-CRITICAL. n=6 anchor not in skynet repo (it cites IIT,
#          not n=6 perfect-number lattice). hexa-os "self-host" is aspirational:
#          freestanding probe skeleton only, no compiled kernel.
# Policy: raw#10 honest scope · raw#12 measure-as-is · raw 77 audit-append.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

