@C hexa_os_l1_local_rules = 5 :: hexa-os.law.local [10*]
  => "5 L1 project-local rules (HOS1..HOS5) inheriting hexa-lang L0 raw."
  => "HOS1 freestanding-only (@nostd attr required in self/os/), HOS2 no .c in kernel path, HOS3 law kernel invariant (every syscall fn must call law_check before real I/O), HOS4 single address space (no user/kernel memory split), HOS5 virtio-only (Phase 1 — no physical HW drivers)."
  => "_meta.inherit=false (HX11 inherit=false — own format). parent = shared/hexa-lang/raw.json."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/.own-rules.json

# ── @F  Facts (hexa-os architecture) ──────────────

@F hexa_os_law_kernel_signature :: hexa-os.law.kernel [10*]
  => "Law kernel core signature: law_check(caller_cap, target, op) — pass → real I/O, fail → EPERM + growth_bus record."
  => "Differentiation: Redox/Linux do DAC/SELinux. hexa-os kernel directly interprets project-specific raw.json (6 rules) + L1 .own-rules.json."
  => "raw.json IS the capability source. growth_bus is the audit log."
  => "Status: design specified, not implemented. Wire-up gated on hexa-lang 3-layer law enforcement (#38+39+29+4) which is 'design complete, wire-up pending'."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/README.md L13-L20 + docs/HEXA_SERVE_V01.md §4

@F hexa_os_unikernel_one_elf :: hexa-os.unikernel [10*]
  => "OS + app = single ELF. `hexa-serve-7b` execution = OS boot + serving start. No kernel/user distinction."
  => "Drivers = virtio only (VM-only). Zero physical hardware drivers."
  => "Workload-specific HARDCODED for 7B LLM inference: fs serves weights only, network = single gRPC/HTTP port, scheduler = prefill/decode 2 tasks. Cannot run web server / DB / general workloads."
  => "Scope-limit IS the speed source. General-purpose loses to Linux. Specialized wins."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/docs/HEXA_SERVE_V01.md §3

@F hexa_os_self_hosting_aspirational :: hexa-os.status [10*FAIL_DOC]
  => "README claims 'Self-hosting — boots 100% in .hexa · freestanding, no libc'."
  => "Honest reality: ONE skeleton file exists — self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa, 28 lines including comments, with placeholder _start() and hexa_main() returning 0. Comment: 'currently skeleton only — does not compile'."
  => "Listed planned files NOT yet present: boot.hexa, kernel.hexa, fs.hexa, drv/, user.hexa."
  => "Prerequisites unmet: hexa-lang P7-9 fixpoint (runtime.c eradication) is the hard gate. README badge says 'stage-design'."
  => "Verdict: ASPIRATIONAL. Not running. Not booting. Not self-hosted. Design + 1 probe skeleton."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa + README.md badge L3

@F hexa_os_three_phase_roadmap :: hexa-os.roadmap [10*]
  => "3-stage realization path: (1) Unikernel 3-6mo (Firecracker guest, single hexa app + minimal kernel), (2) Microkernel 1-2yr (kernel = scheduler + MMU + IPC only; fs/net/drv as user-space hexa daemons), (3) General serving OS 2-3yr (K8s node OS replacement, NVIDIA GPU passthrough, OCI runtime, Linux ABI subset Wine-style)."
  => "Stage-1 proof points: cold-start <500ms, memory footprint <10MB."
  => "Stage-2 proof points: vs Redox p99 ≥20% advantage on AI workload."
  => "Stage-3: confidential compute (SEV/TDX), HBM-as-heap (CXL), law live-update (hot reload raw.json), self-healing kernel."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/ROADMAP.md L5-L48

@F hexa_os_abandoned_scope :: hexa-os.scope.negative [10*]
  => "Explicit abandonments (raw#10 honest scope): general desktop OS (SerenityOS-level 10+ years), NVIDIA closed driver self-write (forever impossible), USB/HID/audio (server-only), RISC-V/TPU/Cerebras (premature investment), Windows ABI (out of scope)."
  => "Hardcore scope discipline. 'Not a Linux replacement' is the README banner — server-side AI inference appliance only."
  |> /Users/ghost/core/hexa-os/ROADMAP.md L60-L66

@F hexa_os_perf_ceiling_training_5pct :: hexa-os.perf.training_cap [9!]
  => "Training gain CEILING: ~5% (compute-bound). GPU compute 85-95% of training time → OS gain 0; NCCL all-reduce kernel-bypass → 0; dataloader 3-5%; checkpoint rare → unmeasurable. Total: ~5% upper bound → 'investment not worthwhile'."
  => "Serving gain: prefill HBM-bound → 0; decode (syscall+scheduler bound) 5-10%; p50 5-10%; p99 30-50%↓ ← real value; QPS at SLA +20-40%; concurrent sessions 2-5×."
  => "Strategic implication: hexa-os explicitly refuses to chase training market. Inference-only positioning is intentional."
